# ==========================================================================
# Central MCP secret references (EXAMPLE) — ONE source of truth for every app.
# --------------------------------------------------------------------------
# These are 1Password op:// REFERENCES, not secrets. It is safe to commit this
# file. The real secret values are never written here — they are resolved at
# launch by the vault-locked `op` service account (vault: vibe_coding ONLY).
#
# How it is used:
#   - Ubuntu / Claude Code:  the login shell snippet runs one `op run --env-file
#     ~/.config/ai-devops/mcp.env` refresh that resolves every reference into the
#     session environment (see setup-secrets.sh — there is no `claude` wrapper).
#   - Windows / Claude Desktop: one mutex-protected `op run` refresh populates a
#     15-minute DPAPI-encrypted user cache shared by all MCP launchers.
#
# References are NAME-based (op://vibe_coding/<item title>/<field>) so they
# survive 1Password account migrations — item UUIDs change, titles do not (this
# file was broken once, 2026-07-22, when a migration re-created every item under
# new UUIDs; see docs/config-inventory.md). A UUID is used ONLY where the item
# title contains parentheses, which `op` rejects in a reference.
#
# setup-secrets.sh (Ubuntu) / setup-machine.ps1 (Windows) copy this file to
#   ~/.config/ai-devops/mcp.env
# Add a new line here when any app introduces a new ${PLACEHOLDER}; every app
# and every machine then picks it up on the next launch. Never inline a value.
# ==========================================================================

# --- Active references (used by app .mcp.json files today) ----------------

# Supabase Personal Access Token — the ONE shared token for ALL POP apps
# (popdam, popcrm-web, poppim-web, monitor, hiclaw, ...). Do not create a
# per-app Supabase token; every app references this same item.
SUPABASE_ACCESS_TOKEN=op://vibe_coding/Supabase CLI Personal Access Token/SUPABASE_ACCESS_TOKEN

# DesignFlow DevOps MCP (https://mcp.designflow.app/mcp) bearer token.
DEVOPS_MCP_TOKEN=op://vibe_coding/designflow-mcp/devops_token

# Synology monitor / NAS MCP (https://nas-mcp.designflow.app/mcp) bearer token.
NAS_MCP_TOKEN=op://vibe_coding/designflow-mcp/nas_token

# Trigger.dev account-level management PAT. Referenced by item id because its
# title has parentheses ("Trigger.dev Personal Access Token (management)"), and
# `op` rejects "(" in a name-based reference. Injected into the `trigger` MCP
# server (and the Ubuntu shell, enabling `npx trigger.dev@latest` CLI auth).
TRIGGER_ACCESS_TOKEN=op://vibe_coding/ylzcsfbhmjyzjy65mnu6uxw67e/credential

# Recall.ai remote MCP (https://us-east-1.recall.ai/mcp) bearer token.
RECALL_AI_MCP_TOKEN=op://vibe_coding/recall-ai MCP/password

# Z.ai GLM Coding Plan key. Used only by ai-glm-agent; the launcher injects it
# into an isolated Claude Code child process and never changes normal Claude or
# Codex authentication. Two traps this reference encodes:
#   1. The key lives in the custom "api key" field, NOT the item's built-in
#      `credential` field, which is EMPTY. `op read`/`op run` of an empty field
#      return "" with exit 0 (a silent empty) — always point at `api key`.
#   2. The title and field label contain spaces. That is fine in this env-file
#      (op takes the whole post-`=` value as the reference, verified via
#      `op run --env-file`); only a bare CLI ref (`op read "op://..."`) needs
#      quoting.
# A silently-empty ZAI_API_KEY previously sent the launcher's re-exec into an
# infinite loop, so the launchers now fail loudly instead (see ai-glm-agent).
ZAI_API_KEY=op://vibe_coding/GLM z.ai API/api key
ZAI_GLM_MODEL=glm-5.2
ZAI_ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL=https://api.z.ai/api/anthropic

# --- Available references (uncomment as an app adopts the placeholder) -----
# GitHub PAT with u2giants push access. Used for git push, not MCP; uncomment
# only if you want it injected into the Claude process environment too.
# GITHUB_TOKEN=op://vibe_coding/GitHub PAT - u2giants repo push access/token
# GH_TOKEN=op://vibe_coding/GitHub PAT - u2giants repo push access/token
